<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-16471] SslTransportLayer may leak SSLEngine resources</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-16471</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;SslTransportLayer&lt;/tt&gt; does not invoke &lt;tt&gt;SSLEngine::closeInbound&lt;/tt&gt; in &lt;tt&gt;close()&lt;/tt&gt; after flushing the &lt;tt&gt;close_notify&lt;/tt&gt; TLS alert.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;While this isn&apos;t a problem for the default JDK SSLEngine, it results in resource leak in Netty/OpenSSL based SSLEngine which frees native resources only when &lt;tt&gt;closeInbound&lt;/tt&gt; is invoked.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
